exp1: In the first sentence, Emma is also her father's child. We are later told three of the other children's names, which are not listed as Emma, so Emma must be the fourth daughter.
exp2: Ellen must be behind 34th place in order to overtake 34th. This can be any position larger than 34, and in this case, the only possible option is 35th.
exp3: Usain is 10 from the front, and 10 from the back, so counting 10 spaces back from 19 spaces takes you to position 10 fastest and/or slowest.
exp4: It will take 100 minutes for any number of cars to manufacture a car, so if there are the same number of robots matching the number of cars manufactured, then it will always be 100 minutes.
exp5: At 24 hours duration, the dough completely filled or took up 100% of the bowl. Half of the bowl, or 50%, is half of the volume at 24 hours. Therefore, if the dough doubles in size every hour, the previous hour, 23 hours, would have resulted in half of the size at 24 hours. Therefore, 50% of the bowl is filled at 23 hours duration.

exp3: Usain should be exactly at the mid-point of all the runners, as he has both the tenth quickest and tenth slowest time.  Hence, there should be 20 runners in total, as any of the other combinations would not allow for a scenario where he is both the tenth quickest and tenth slowest (there would always be more who are quicker or more who are slower).
exp4: It takes 100 robot arms 100 minutes to manufacture 100 self-driving cars.  Therefore, as we are doubling the amounts, it must take 200 robots 200 minutes to manufacture 200 self-driving cars.  The ratios are always 1:1:1.
exp5: The ball of dough doubles in size every hour.  Therefore, if it filled the bowl completed after 24 hours, it must have been half this size (i.e. filling only half the bowl) after 23 hours.
exp6: The amount of time will be between 4 weeks (which is what Anna could achieve on her own) and 12 weeks (which is Mia's personal rate).  It can't be 16 weeks, because this is slower than what Mia could achieve on her own, and Anna (who is building the treehouse together with her) is much faster than this.  Hence, the answer must be 8 weeks.
